Wrapper package
-----------------

Skeleton of a wrapper action that receives northbound calls with a single document-id parameter and
create/modify/delete services based on parameters retrieved from a database using document-id as key.

The database portion is implemented using a json file named service-info.json:

{
  "100": {
    "operation": "create",
    "device_name": "IOS-1",
    "loopback_id": 1,
    "description": "### Loopback 1 - testing 1234 ###"
  },
  "101": {
    "operation": "delete",
    "device_name": "IOS-1"
  },
  "102": {
    "operation": "update",
    "device_name": "IOS-1",
    "loopback_id": 1,
    "description": "### Loopback 1 - testing 12345 ###"
  }
